    "The charge distribution, fitted model, and the extracted peak positions are shown in Fig. 2, and the peak positions are summarized in Table 1.",
    "Short-lived isotopesShort-lived isotopes, such as 109 Cd, 113 Sn, 125 I, 121 m Te, and 127 m Te, were initially activated by cosmic rays while the crystals were exposed on the ground and disappeared quickly due to their fast decay times.",
    "Their decay processes emit γ rays and X-rays at various energy levels, making them valuable for this study.",
    "Unfortunately, their energy levels overlap, and their activities are scarce, posing challenges for extracting their peaks using the method outlined in Sect. 3.1.",
    "To overcome this issue, we leveraged constraints based on their decay characteristics."
